Boipelo.MereTHIS year marks the 19th instalment of the Mangaung African Cultural Festival (Macufe), a music extravaganza staged annually in Mangaung, Bloemfontein. This year s edition will be from Friday (30/09) till Sunday, 9 October, culminating in the football match between arch-rivals Bloemfontein Celtic and Kaizer Chiefs who will be battling it out for the Macufe Cup.This year s theme is Igniting the African Spirit.This year s music line-up includes award-winning Andy Narell (USA), whose steel pan prowess earned him world popularity. Headlining the line-up will be songbird Karyn White of Superwoman fame, also from the USA. Living up to the theme, the event will be graced by Roneo Mputu from the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC). The Free State Department of Sports, Arts, Culture and Recreation, spared no effort in its support for Macufe as the region s economy thrives during this week-long event. Macufe is proudly supported by the National Department of Arts and Culture, Standard Bank, National Lotteries Commission, Mangaung Metro Municipality, Free State Tourism, Lesedi FM, The New Age and ANN7. The week-long series of the Macufe events will kick-start with Tshepe versus the New Age Squad of Hip Hop on Friday at The Dome, Old Grey sports ground, from 18:00 to 02:00. Tickets at Compu-ticket and Shoprite/Checkers. Visit www.macufe.co.za for the programme.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.